This Oyster Perpetual Datejust 41 in Oystersteel and white gold features a bright blue, fluted dial and a Jubilee bracelet.


Fluted


The fluted is a graphic interpretation of an iconic Rolex design element: the bezel fluting found exclusively on some of the brand’s Classic watches.


Made from age-old materials, combined with cutting-edge technology, the fluted dial brings depth and sophistication to the timeless Datejust.


A Rolex signature


The Rolex fluted bezel is a mark of distinction. Originally, the fluting of the Oyster bezel had a functional purpose: it served to screw the bezel onto the case helping to ensure the waterproofness of the watch.


It was therefore identical to the fluting on the case back, which was also screwed onto the case for waterproofness, using specific Rolex tools. Over time, the fluting became an aesthetic element, a genuine Rolex signature feature. Today the fluted bezel is a mark of distinction, in gold on this Datejust 41.


A meeting of two metals


Gold is coveted for its lustre and nobility. Steel reinforces strength and reliability. Together, they harmoniously combine the best of their properties.


A true Rolex signature, Rolesor has featured on Rolex models since the early 1930s, and was trademarked as a name in 1933. It is one of the prominent pillars of the Oyster collection.


Supple and comfortable


The design, development and production of Rolex bracelets and clasps, as well as the stringent tests they face, involve advanced high technology.


And, as with all the components of the watch, aesthetic controls by the human eye guarantee impeccable beauty. The Jubilee, a supple and comfortable five-piece link metal bracelet, was designed and made especially for the launch of the Oyster Perpetual Datejust in 1945.

Movement/Caliber: 3235, Manufacture Rolex


Water resistance: Waterproof to 100 metres / 330 feet


Bracelet: Jubilee, five-piece links

Seiko automatic with manual wind men's watch SRPD29K1. The mechanical movement 4R36 of the SRPD29 with a number of 24 jewels has the functions: hour, minute, second, date, weekday. Made of stainless steel, this is waterproof tested to 20 bar / 200 m. The silver dial is protected by a scratch resistant hardlex glass. The diameter of the SRPD29 measured without the crown is about 44 mm. The housing height is 13 mm. The Gangrereserve in this automatic clock is fully charged> 41h.

Features:

Automatic movement Caliber: 4R36 analog 24 jewels

Watch glass: scratch-resistant, hardened mineral glass / hard glass with date magnifier

Elevator mechanism: Double-sided automatic winding (magic lever)

Water resist: 20 bar

Dial: black dial with applied, highly polished stainless steel indexes. The indices are filled in with luminescent Lumibrite luminescent mass

Hands: Stainless steel hour hand, minute hand and second hand. All hands are also coated with Lumibrite luminescent material for easy readability in the dark

Belt clasp: Safety folding clasp with safety handles and safety bar with engraved Seiko lettering

Magnetic resistance: 4800 A / m (amperes per meter)

Band: black ion-plated stainless steel bracelet with additional diver extension

Bracelet width: The bracelet width of the stainless steel band is 20,0 - 27,2 mm (measured at the band stop)

Display: hour, minute, second, date and weekday (weekday display in German / English)

Housing: Stainless steel housing with dark gray titanium carbide support and screwed stainless steel bottom

Special feature: one-sided rotatable, precisely locking bezel

Power reserve: greater 41 hours power reserve

Bracelet length: The bracelet length is about 215 mm

Case diameter (without crown) 42 mm

Case height: 13 mm

Weight: The Seiko Monster SRPD29 weighs 187 grams
